  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Fresh out of a near-fatal scrape with a Necron tomb world, Cain is seconded to the Reclaimers — an archaeotech-obsessed Space Marine chapter — as Commissariat liaison while they sail to Viridia to suppress a noble-led civil war. The unrest turns out to be a genestealer cult and the Reclaimers' next mission is tracking down the space hulk that brought it. The boarding action goes badly: most of the Marines are devoured by the awakening Tyranid presence inside the hulk, and Cain is left to navigate its lightless corridors with Jurgen, a stowaway band of Orks, and the Viridian Governor's spoiled, infatuated daughter Mira. The novel is the first time Cain serves alongside Astartes for a sustained stretch, and he is — predictably — unimpressed and grateful to make it home. The seventh Cain memoir.",
